content.detailedDescription: I was sat in the back garden watching a storm building when my attention was drawn to a spherical object high up in the sky, it was darker than the dark storm clouds behind it and changed colour from grey to black, it caught my attention because it was stationary and was  for several minutes as the storm built behind it. as i watched it moved eastwards very slowly and stopped on several occasions hovering in the sky. the object continued eastward and then turned and headed back into the storm disappearing into the clouds for approx. 2-3 minutes before appearing again at a lower altitude where again it hovered and appeared to be spinning, as i watched it moved slowly east again before stopping and then taking off at a terrific speed eastwards and ascended into the clouds before i lost sight of it
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Black sphere hovering in storm moved slowly stopped changed direction and left at speed

content.detailedDescription:
I was working at the local middle school when this happened. i had the take trash out to the dumpster and i often like to look at the sky to watch the clouds. i noticed this craft, very silver and metallic looking,no noise, almost like an oval cigar shape, and it was doing these impossible maneuvers. it would turn sharply and change its trajectory. normal planes and helicopters would never be able to preform these moves. that is what caught my attention. 
the craft kept doing these amazing twists and turns for about 5 mins. it eventually disappeared into the clouds without making a noise. never saw it again after that.
content.summary: Ufo made impossible movements for around 5 mins, then disappeared into the clouds.

content.detailedDescription: At 10pm on tuesday july 19th 2016 i was leaving my grandmother in laws underground parade here in south surrey. as i drove up i looked strait at the twilight eastern sky and above the houses i saw a smooth blinking blue-white light making a sweeping turn from south east to east. within a few seconds of watching it, the object appeared to disappear in a short streak of light. i could see the light had a dark ball behind it. i grew up on a flight path and am familiar with aircraft and i've seen plenty of drones with led lights, this was none of these. it's movement was so smooth that if i were watching it on a video i would have sworn it was cgi.  i'd say it was 1000 to 1500 feet off the ground and a block and a half away. the blinking light was a crisp blue white in colour but when it shot away the brief light streak had warmer faint yellow orange in the blue. anyway, it made my skin crawl when i saw it.
content.summary: Blinking blue light that zipped away leaving a brief streak

content.detailedDescription:
Last night i was walking to my car and noticed a glowing white orb ufo moving ne to e over the skies of oakwood ga ... what caught my eye was the fact it was glowing very bright and has no flashing lights like a normal airplane would. i observed it moving slowly from left to right for approx 10 - 15 seconds ... immediately when realizing what i was seeing was obviously a ufo of some kind it simply disintegrated before my eyes. there was absolutely no sounds coming from orb or the woods directly behind the house and every hair on my body stood up for almost a minute as i just kept repeating to myself, "what just happened?" ...

as i walked to the door stunned, i heard two distinct loud knocking sounds coming from the woods ... not trying to be funny when i say the knocking sounds were almost "alien" and i still have no idea what the sounds were.

included is a picture from the area where the ufo was witnessed the next day...
content.summary: Last night i observed an orb ufo over oakwood ga... witnessed for approx 15 seconds as it moved left to right then disintegrated ....

content.detailedDescription: I was in my house, windows open when i heard a loud helicopter approaching.  i ran out on my back porch and saw a red light or orb high in the air fly directly over my house from east to west, then a low flying helicopter following behind it.  they were both flying exact same direction at about the same speed but the copter was much lower than the light/orb.  they flew out of sight, due to trees the observation was approx 10 seconds.  unable to see color of copter due to darkness but it was large, and very loud, it also seemed to be much lower than the object and followed directly behind it.  i have no idea what it was, id did not have an outline which made me think it was just a light or orb, it traveled straight and had a consistant speed. i felt afraid as if the military was chasing this unknown object.  after it passed and was out of sight i went up to my wife and told her but she laughed.  i know what i saw and it wasnt a plane, or another copter, it didnt seem to make any noise as i just heard the noise of the copter.  lost sight of the object through the trees.  it happened too quick to video and i was kind of in awe of what i saw and didnt even think to grab my phone.
content.summary: Solid red light followed behind by a low flying helicopter

content.detailedDescription:
My girlffriend and i were at the metlife stadium on june 17th 2016 to watch one of the copa america's quater final. about 15 minutes before the game, my gf saw these 3 dots coming slowly over the stadium. its hard to say how high these 3 were and i thought they were balloons or mabe drones to film the game.
then these black 3 dots stayed in formation and i started to really wonder what these were, so i took my iphone out and was able to film the last 7 second of this sighting.
if you look carefully, the left black dot shows as silver at the 3rd second. then at the 4th second, the top one does it too. i didn't realize it until i watched the the video in still mode.
then at the end of the video, you'd think they are descending but they are actually going up really fast. i was really surprised by that and i moved my phone too fast toward the up side. i lost it from sight in a second or so.
in any case, that was pretty cool to see these 3 dots coming from nowhere and disapear right over the stadium.
i hope someone else saw that, we were close to 80000 people in the stadium for that event.
content.summary: 3 black dots stay in formation coming over the metlife stadium and disapear in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I was driving in my car on a1a heading north in daytona beach florida, jut prior to granada blvd, at 8:15pm on 7-19-16, a little over one hour ago. i looked up in the sky towards the west, approximately 40 degrees up and saw an extremely bright (silver) object about 1,000 ft up, just even with the first very dense layer of three small grey clouds. the sky was very clear and my first thought is that it was an airplane reflecting the rays of the sun. i kept my eye on the object for close to 10 seconds. the sky was fairly clear in all directions and in the very far distance i could see airplanes flying the normal flight routes, very faint but visible airplanes. after the ten second constant watch,the object vanished from sight. i said to my wife, "what the hell was that?'i explained what i saw, we pulled over to the west of a1a so i could attempt to locate what i thought was an airplane and track the aircraft with my eye. with a very clear 180 degree view of the western sky i could not see nor could my wife see any aircraft heading west, north, east or south. i was stationary at this location for 10 minutes looking for any signs of a possible aircraft. once again, the sky was very clear and cloud coverage was minimal. this very bright silver object vanished from sight. nothing came through the three small grey clouds and i never saw it again.
content.summary: Very bright silver object vanished from site.

content.detailedDescription:
where were you and what were you doing at the time? i was riding motorcycle,  heading east, and looking at the beautiful full moon. 

2. what made you first notice the object? it looked like an airplane fuselage, but was hovering, or moving very slowly at least,  below the moons relative position at the time. it was also very high, possibly  in low earth orbit, even tho it was still light out, i thought maybe the suns very low position might have made it visible. 

3. what did you think the object was when you first noticed it? an airplane until i realized no wings or tail, then blimp or balloon but it appeared to be made of metal or something reflective. then i realized it was moving to the east and appeared to be moving more rapidly and getting harder to see like the sun was not reflecting on it as much so i thought it might be the iss until i checked nasa sight for visible sighting listings, and it was over africa at that time


4. describe the object and its actions and motions in detail. it was either chrome/metallic or white but i'm pretty sure it was a metal object. 

5. describe your feelings, reactions and actions, during and after sighting the object. just curious as to what it was. i'm guessing some type of experimental air or spacecraft, but it's possible it was a satellite reflecting sunlight

6. how did you lose sight of the object? it got harder to find, since i was driving a motorcycle it was a little harder to focus on it, and i kept losing it due to trees etc. eventually i couldn't find it, it appeared to be gaining speed /altitude but it never really moved very fast

the oddest thing about it was, it appeared to me as the broadside of an airplane or rocket... the long way... although i couldn't make out whether it had an airplane like nose or not.. but it was traveling sideways, by that i mean it appeared as a jet would appear flying north and south, but it was moving east. that's why i noticed it, otherwise i'd have thought it was just an airplane. also, the full moon was out, but it was still light out, right at sunset

it would have appeared to be over wisconsin /minnesota  / iowa at about 20:15 sunday evening, 7/17/2016
content.summary: Looked like metallic plane fuselage, minus wings and tail. hovered or was moving relatively slow then headed east still slowly, but was drifting sideways

content.detailedDescription:
I was on holiday in turkish town bodrum-küçükbük on august 2014. bodrum is a city with a high ufo activity. when i was at the balcony of a home a local person showed me a starlike object in the sky and told me that it was regularly appearing. it was approximately 8:10 pm and the sky was not dark. stars were not visible yet. 
when i firstly saw the object i though it could be a plane but it had different features. it was suddenly appearing -like somebody turned on a lightbulb-. it had dark orange color and moving with a liner direction. then after approximately one minute passed it disappeared.-just like somebody turned the lightbulb off- this suprised me very much because these were not things a plane would do.
next day i saw it again at the same time at the same place with the same features. this time i had my camera with me so i took a few photos of it. it was flying high and over a hill where telecommunication tower was standing. it was it's regular place. this regularly appearing object stopped appearing after a few days. but the observation was very  exciting and unique experience. 

regards
content.summary: Starlike object suddenly appearing at the same time

content.detailedDescription: Hi, i am and avid astronomer and i take a lot of pictures of the milkyway when the moon is dark. so i don't pay much attention to the full moon sky. tonight on my way to work as i was  mars i saw a ufo. this craft was fast moving and very high it was moving east to west against the jet stream. i live in upstate western ny near rochester ny. there are a lot of air traffic heading west to east low and on approach to the rochester airport. they usually having landing lights on and a blinking tail and wing tip lights. the craft i saw had to have been moving a thousand miles an hour and the lights were blinking in a fast strobe fashion going from white to red. the craft was gone in less than 10 seconds. the sky was fully lit from the moon so i can rule out a satellite. only ♂ and a few stars were visible, it was 1030 pm. i have observed a lot of craft in the night sky and this was unlike anything i have ever seen, i am an air force vet so i know a lot about military craft this was not military.
content.summary: Fast moving craft seen above the city of batavia with pulsing lights.

content.detailedDescription:
1. where were you and what were you doing at the time?
i was in my front yard at 8:30pm looking at the sky with my head on a swivel, as usual, at the specific time.

2. what made you first notice the object? 
the slow and/or no speed of the object and no noise from it that i could detect. object never exceeded the speed of a cessna and was cessna sized or slightly bigger, i'm guessing by the size of its lights.

3. what did you think the object was when you first noticed it? 
with no noise and the ability to come to a dead stop, i thought it was an et-ufo for the first 5 seconds of seeing it then i had second thoughts. object had regulation faa navigation lights that never broke sequence. object never broke its altitude. object never broke its slow counterclockwise orbit or orbit diameter until it finally left, at cessna speed, in straight line path, headed due s then headed due e, at 9:53pm. object never made any crazy ufo moves.
 
4. describe the object and its actions and motions in detail.
when i first saw the object it was approaching the sw corner of its 5-10 mile wide orbit at about 10,000 feet. the sw corner of its orbit was nearly directly over my house, where it would come to a dead stop for 15-30 seconds on each orbit it made, with no noise that i could detect. i'm guessing it completed about 6-8 orbits over the 1 hour and 11 minutes that i watched it, until it finally departed the area at cessna speed.

5. describe your feelings, reactions and actions, during and after sighting the object.
i was waiting for it to make "an et-ufo move" but it never did.

6. how did you lose sight of the object? 
object finally broke its orbits at 9:53pm and headed due s over orange county then made a turn heading due e. when the object broke its orbit and headed s it damn near flew exactly between me and a full moon allowing me to see its entire outline, back-lit by the moon. skies were cloudless and visibility was unlimited. i had a split second to see what outline that i could see but it was not saucer shaped. whatever it was it was very skinny. stick-like. i'm about 99% positive it was some type of unknown(to me), man-made, v/stol, fixed wing, usaf drone. i heard zero noise of any rotor chop coming from it. it was basically silent at its altitude level.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: 8:42pm-9:53pm: silent or nearly silent object with faa regulation nav lights and hovering ability in a 5-10 mile wide counterclockwise orbit over south la at 10,000 feet.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking around the neighborhood, it was starting to get darker outside and i tend to look at the night sky frequently. i saw what i thought to be a comet, but it seemed to be under the atmosphere... as i watched it, it split into two separate comet-like flying air crafts, or so i believe, and then both changed direction at a 90 degree angle and both went separate ways. as i watched them fly off they kept going at the same direction as when they split off, and then about halfway across the sky to the treeline, they dissepated into thin air. never seen anything like that before. immediately i went to the house and searched around on the internet for reports of comets or other celestial objects splitting in two like that and could not find anything.
content.summary: Comet-like aircraft, split into two individual aircrafts and both changed direction.
